summary: And the truth is, Kilgrave doesn’t really understand that he— a lot of the things he did were as bad as they were. Which, again,...
body:
And the truth is, Kilgrave doesn’t really understand that he— a lot of the things he did were as bad as they were. Which, again, goes back to the conversations we had. It’s about responsibility. Obviously, that was in a world where he had a supernatural power and he could… you know, part of his issue was that he wasn’t able to detect consent from anyone, because he, whenever he asked someone to do something, they did it, and therefore, you know, he couldn’t unpick that.

David Tennant (BUILDSeries.com interview 9/10/18)

summary: So, I’m not sure if this is already explained somewhere, but I had a thought about how the Doctor regenerates and how it always...
body:
The Doctor Regenerates Wrong

So, I’m not sure if this is already explained somewhere, but I had a thought about how the Doctor regenerates and how it always leaves them a little…

…loopy.

The Doctor isn’t one to do things by the book, and I think the regeneration process is meant to take longer than the Doctor allows. If we look at another regeneration. In Hell Bent the General regenerates, and says it’s his 10th regeneration. (or he’s currently on his 10th. Either way.) When we see the regeneration process, it’s a lot more controlled than the Doctors.

And after the process is over, the new General is basically fine and right back to business. I think the light that envelopes the regenerating Time Lord is meant to stick around longer and repair the whole body and mind until they get up and carry on. The Doctor is too impatient for that, so as soon as they’re done with the body changing, they just let the rest of the regeneration happen while they’re off on the next adventure.

I might be way off, I admit. But to me it just makes sense that while the Doctor regenerates, all that’s on their mind is…

summary: the first time i saw david tennant was as barty crouch jr in harry potter and the goblet of fire and for me this role was really...
body:
the first time i saw david tennant was as barty crouch jr in harry potter and the goblet of fire and for me this role was really interesting because it was different and a little bit weird (and i love everything that’s different and weird.) and i didn’t know david at this time, but i liked his character most in the film. years later i started watching doctor who and ten became my favourite doctor, who is also played by david and he became my favourite actor. one time when i watched hp 4 again i just realized: the role i like so much because of the difference is played by david tennant, the actor i love with all my heart and i just liked him before i knew him and when i knew him i started loving him.

yeah, and that’s my story about becoming a fan of david tennant. what about you?
